headline: EMCOR (NYSE:EME) Beats Q1 Sales Targets, Full-Year Outlook Slightly Exceeds Expectations
summary: Specialty construction contractor company EMCOR (NYSE:EME) announced better-than-expected revenue in Q1 CY2025, with sales up 12.7% year on year to $3.87 billion. The company’s full-year revenue guidance of $16.5 billion at the midpoint came in 0.8% above analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $5.41 per share was 17% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
